{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"75545a9a-741b-415d-bf8e-2d44eae1f33e","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The second form does an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"edd6ced6-eaaa-4273-949b-04f35ef44fca","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question about dotnet CLI usage - I can answer directly without needing to look at files.","outputTokens":165,"requestId":"BD20:2EBD81:20A7897:2548130:6A07E08B"},"id":"4b6d6e48-d970-430b-858f-01c1b80a0541","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:12:16.496Z","parentId":"db47c78d-8287-4585-8d0c-31b91bad352a"}
